<title>
B-Pillar Outer Panel, Rear Door Hinge Reinforcement and Center Pillar Inner Panel Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The figure below shows condition where following parts are removed.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front fender 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9A06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0083.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "55.869mm" ver = "02" gw = "227" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A9B06013001">
<title>
General Notes
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Welding method and number of welding points are the same on both sides. This repair instruction shows procedure for left side.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Part filled with foamed material is included in parts of this repair. Therefore, repair referring to 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A9B06022">Foamed Material Filling Area Repair</intxref>
 for precautions and repair procedure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The dimensions shown in the figure are reference values when cutting replacement part placed on top of existing part. Determine most appropriate cutting (or joint) line considering both size of replacement part and condition of existing part.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A9B06013002">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mark at the shown position and cut B-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
You may accidentally cut the parts under the roof panel or the parts under the side sill outer panel when cutting the B-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Take sufficient care not to damage the parts under the roof panel or the parts under the side sill outer panel when cutting the B-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Cut B-pillar outer panel, rear door hinge reinforcement and outer pillar inner panel at the same time at shown rough cutting position.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots and remove B-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0114.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "147.989mm" ver = "02" gw = "482" gh = "403"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.475in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "4.172in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.198in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "2.277in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
When heating around foamed material application portion to detach foamed material, be sure that temperature of said portion does not reach 170 &#176;C (338 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
B-pillar outer panel cut position (Cut around here)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots and remove upper part of rear door hinge upper reinforcement and upper part of center pillar inner panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0115.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.210mm" ver = "01" gw = "228" gh = "114"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots and remove lower part of rear door hinge lower reinforcement.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0116.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.891mm" ver = "01" gw = "234" gh = "105"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots and remove lower part of center pillar inner panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0117.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.519mm" ver = "01" gw = "233" gh = "113"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A9B06013003">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before conducting any weld, check installation position and condition for installation part(s). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9B04006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 / 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9B04007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Proceed repair while taking into consideration installation of parts that affect appearance. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9B04003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install rear door hinge retainers (2 pcs.).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0118.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "130.636mm" ver = "02" gw = "227" gh = "354"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install center pillar inner panel.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Conduct plug weld.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0119.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "61.309mm" ver = "01" gw = "226" gh = "157"/>
</figure>
<figure page = "2">
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0120.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "73.141mm" ver = "02" gw = "227" gh = "191"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install rear door hinge upper reinforcement and rear door hinge lower reinforcement.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Conduct plug weld or resistance spot weld.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0121.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.585mm" ver = "01" gw = "219" gh = "155"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0122.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "72.222mm" ver = "02" gw = "215" gh = "188"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Install new B-pillar outer panel to vehicle body and cut in stacked condition.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Repair the position of B-pillar outer panel where foamed material had been filled. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9B06022"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Install B-pillar outer panel to vehicle body.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Conduct plug weld or resistance spot weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Conduct continuous weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply anticorrosion wax to back side of continuous weld part.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A9B0011.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "196.084mm" ver = "01" gw = "490" gh = "539"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "6" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.472in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "2.800in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.197in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.535in"/>
<colspec colnum = "5" colname = "5" colwidth = "0.197in"/>
<colspec colnum = "6" colname = "6" colwidth = "1.974in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld as three panel thickness.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
B-pillar outer panel
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "5" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "6" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Side sill strength
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Foamed material
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Rear door hinge reinforcement
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "5" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
</entry>
<entry colname = "6" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
